main event: A stationary unidentified object was observed in Cunningham, Tennessee on 15 October 1956.
interesting points: The object was the size of a car's silhouette reflected on the ground,It remained stationary before moving,The second sighting involved the object moving in a straight line at a 180-degree azimuth and 45-degree elevation,Observers used binoculars to track the object for 20 minutes,The witnesses mentioned the object reappeared at 23:06Z in the same direction as before.
sighted object: an unidentified object resembling a balloon
witness description: no specific witness details provided in file
